-- U.S. firm Ripplewood takes stake in Egypt's SODIC -source
-- By Ehab Farouk
-- Thu May 08, 2014 03:46AM EDT
-- None



CAIRO, May 8 (Reuters) - U.S Investment group Ripplewood has acquired a 10 percent stake in Egyptian property developer SODIC <OCDI.CA>, a source informed about the deal told Reuters on Thursday.

"Ripplewood bought a 10 percent stake in SODIC's shares," the source said.